snippet: Twin blasts in Baghdad, plus an attack in a police station, showed the seriousness of Iraq’s struggle with insurgents more than seven months after the last American troops left the country.
abstract: Twin car bombs explode in central Baghdad, killing at least 19 people, and Iraqi security forces fight off an attack inside a police station by two suicide bombers trying to free jailed insurgents; assaults underscore the seriousness of Iraq's struggle with insurgents more than seven months after the last American troops departed.
lead_paragraph: Twin blasts in Baghdad, plus an attack in a police station, showed the seriousness of Iraq’s struggle with insurgents more than seven months after the last American troops left the country.
